<br>
I disagree. You take a look at what my guild does on a raid in ToV-N or VP and I don't think you'll be saying anyone can do it. We work as a unit and learning to do that takes time, effort and instinct. To handle the stresses associated with a large raiding guild takes a certain type of personality. To get along in a guild of this size takes tolerance. To make it up through the loot/seniority order takes patience and dedication.<br>
<br>
Many people can play their class well, the trick is playing your class well AND knowing how to play your class to most benefit the others in your raid. I'm not saying this is rocket science, but instinct plays a major role in succeeding at EQ.<br>
<br>
It's easy to sit back and say &quot;anyone can do what EV/Comps do with enough time&quot;, but I promise you, it takes ALOT more than free time to get to this level of play. <p><br>
